\title{The flick: a unit of time}
\taxon{reference}
\date{2018}
\meta{external}{https://github.com/OculusVR/Flicks}
\meta{author}{Christopher Horvath (Facebook/Oculus)}

\p{C. Horvath. \em{Flicks: a unit of time}. Facebook/Oculus, 2018. A flick is #{1/705{,}600{,}000} second (#{= 2^6 \cdot 3^2 \cdot 5^4 \cdot 7^2} in the denominator). Designed so that all standard frame rates and audio sample rates have integer flick counts per sample. Open source, public domain.}
